			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">These days, NaClLog(LOG_FATAL,...) exits the process by doing NaClAbort().  On Unix, that calls abort(), but on Windows it calls NaClExit().  We should ensure that this triggers a Breakpad crash report in Chrome instead.

NaCl has its own implementations of CHECK() and DCHECK(), which use NaClLog()+LOG_FATAL.  We want to ensure that failures of these checks trigger crash reports too.
